SIMPLE: subject-matter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subject-matter
<hw>Sub"ject-mat`ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The matter or
thought presented for consideration in some statement or discussion;
that which is made the object of thought or study.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As to the <qex>subject-matter</qex>, words are always to be
understood as having a regard thereto.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As science makes progress in any <qex>subject-matter</qex>, poetry
recedes from it.</q> <rj><qau>J. H. Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subjectness</ent>⟦br⟧
